Kataskeve (assets/libs/kataskeve.js) is an in-house elementary Euclidean
geometry diagram renderer authored as part of the md-previewer project. It
is an ORIGINAL implementation and does NOT incorporate, derive from,
translate, or copy any code from the GPL-licensed Eukleides tool
(https://www.eukleides.org/) or from the unrelated npm package "euclid.js"
(or any other geometry library).

Mathematical constructions used internally (midpoint, foot of perpendicular,
circle through three points, orthocenter, line/circle intersection, etc.)
are textbook Euclidean geometry and are not subject to copyright. The
implementation, source language design, parser, evaluator, and SVG renderer
were developed independently for this project.

The name "Kataskeve" is the Greek κατασκευή ("construction"), the term
Euclid used in the Elements for the construction step of a proposition.
Earlier working titles (both withdrawn): "euclid" (collided with the npm
package euclid.js) and "sakuzu" (collided with the Microsoft Store UWP app
"Sakuzu", a Windows diagram-creation tool in the same product category).

It is distributed under the same license as md-previewer. See the top-level
LICENSE file for the applicable terms.
